# Testing Conventions

## Stack

- **Runner**: Vitest with `environment: 'happy-dom'`
- **Mount**: `@vue/test-utils` for Vue components
- **Location**: `__tests__/` folder next to the source file

```
app/composables/useAuthSession.ts
app/composables/__tests__/useAuthSession.test.ts
```

## File Naming

- `*.test.ts` or `*.spec.ts`
- Mirror the source file name: `useFeature.ts` → `useFeature.test.ts`

## Composable Tests

Test composables directly without mounting a component when possible:

```ts
import { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from "vitest";
import { useAuthSession } from "../useAuthSession";

describe("useAuthSession", () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    // reset reactive state here
  });

  it("returns null when no session exists", () => {
    const { session } = useAuthSession();
    expect(session.value).toBeNull();
  });
});
```

## Component Tests

```ts
import { mount } from "@vue/test-utils";
import MyComponent from "../MyComponent.vue";

it("renders the title", () => {
  const wrapper = mount(MyComponent, { props: { title: "Hello" } });
  expect(wrapper.text()).toContain("Hello");
});
```

## Commands

```bash
pnpm test          # single run
pnpm test:watch    # watch mode
pnpm test:coverage # coverage report
```

## Rules

- Group related assertions with `describe`; use `beforeEach` to reset state.
- Test composables directly (no component mount) whenever possible.
- Tests must pass before deploy — do not skip or mock core business logic.
- Update or add minimal tests when behavior changes.
